HEADWORD: cattleya
<hw>cattleya</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any orchid of the genus
<gen>Cattleya</gen> characterized by a hood-shaped three-lobed lip
enclosing the column; they are among the most popular and most
extravagantly beautiful orchids known. Called also <altname>cattleya
orchid</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

